Detailed Description

Contains data about a cellular phone.

When packed into or from a packet UserCellular looks like this. The first TYPE_CELLULAR and Total size in bytes and the last TYPE_CELLULAR is read by someone else when read from a packet. {tabular}{lll} Pos & Size & Destription \ pos & 1 bytes & TYPE_CELLULAR \ +1 & 2 bytes & Total size in bytes \ +3 & 1 bytes & TYPE_CELLULAR \ +4 & 2 bytes & Total size in bytes \ +6 & 4 bytes & ID \ +10 & 1 bytes & smsParams \ +11 & 2 bytes & maxSearchHitsWap \ +13 & 2 bytes & maxRouteLinesWap \ +15 & 1 bytes & smsService \ +16 & 1 bytes & wapService \ +17 & 4 bytes & EOLType \ +21 & 1 bytes & smsLineLength \ +22 & 2 bytes & phoneNumberLength \ +24 & string & phoneNumber \ & 2 bytes & modelNameLength\ & string & modelName \ & data & CellularPhoneModel \ last-1 & 1 bytes & TYPE_CELLULAR \ last & 1 bytes & TYPE_CELLULAR \ {tabular}
